http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Man-surrenders-after-killing-wife/article14026332.ece

A 45-year-old man Dastagiri Basha surrendered at Duvvur police station after axing his wife Mabu Vali, 40, to death at his house in Krishnampalle village of Kadapa district on Thursday.Trust deficitDastagiri Basha, who has two sons and two daughters, confessed to have killed his wife suspecting her fidelity, Duvvur Sub-Inspector Madhusudan Reddy told mediapersons.Mydukur Rural Circle Inspector Nagabhushanam inspected Basha’s house where his wife’s body lied in a pool of blood.Police shifted the body to hospital for post-mortem.